  "prompt": "Where in North America is area code 632?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, **area code 632** is **not currently assigned** to any geographic region within the North American Numbering Plan (NANP). The NANP encompasses the United States, Canada, several Caribbean countries, and other territories in North America, and area codes are subject to change based on demand and administrative decisions.\n\n**Possible Reasons for Inquiry:**\n\n1. **Future Assignments:** Area codes are periodically introduced to accommodate growing populations and the increasing demand for telephone numbers. It's possible that 632 has been reserved for future use or is under consideration for assignment.\n\n2. **Non-Geographic Use:** Some area codes are designated for specific purposes rather than geographic regions, such as for services like VoIP or toll-free numbers. However, 632 doesn't currently fall into this category within the NANP.\n\n3. **Typographical Error:** If you intended to inquire about a different area code (e.g., 236, 362, etc.), please double-check the number for more accurate information.\n\n**Next Steps:**\n\n- **Check Official Sources:** For the most up-to-date and accurate information, consult the [North American Numbering Plan Administration (NANPA)](https://www.nationalnanpa.com/) or your local telecommunications provider.\n\n- **Monitor Updates:** Area code assignments can change, so staying informed through official channels will ensure you have the latest details.\n\nIf you have any other questions or need information on a different area code, feel free to ask!",
